<div class=3D"td-content">
	<h1>minikube start</h1>
 =20
	<header class=3D"article-meta">
	=09
</header>
	<p>minikube is local Kubernetes, focusing on making it easy to learn and d=
evelop for Kubernetes.</p>
<p>All you need is Docker (or similarly compatible) container or a Virtual =
Machine environment, and Kubernetes is a single command away: <code>minikub=
e start</code></p>
<h2 id=3D"what-youll-need">What you=E2=80=99ll need</h2>
<ul>
<li>2 CPUs or more</li>
<li>2GB of free memory</li>
<li>20GB of free disk space</li>
<li>Internet connection</li>
<li>Container or virtual machine manager, such as: <a href=3D"https://minik=
ube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/drivers/docker/">Docker</a>, <a href=3D"https://miniku=
be.sigs.k8s.io/docs/drivers/qemu/">QEMU</a>, <a href=3D"https://minikube.si=
gs.k8s.io/docs/drivers/hyperkit/">Hyperkit</a>, <a href=3D"https://minikube=
.sigs.k8s.io/docs/drivers/hyperv/">Hyper-V</a>, <a href=3D"https://minikube=
.sigs.k8s.io/docs/drivers/kvm2/">KVM</a>, <a href=3D"https://minikube.sigs.=
k8s.io/docs/drivers/parallels/">Parallels</a>, <a href=3D"https://minikube.=
sigs.k8s.io/docs/drivers/podman/">Podman</a>, <a href=3D"https://minikube.s=
igs.k8s.io/docs/drivers/virtualbox/">VirtualBox</a>, or <a href=3D"https://=
minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/drivers/vmware/">VMware Fusion/Workstation</a></l=
i>
