yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
-shell" data-lang=3D"shell">minikube start
</code></pre><div class=3D"toolbar"><div class=3D"toolbar-item"><button cla=
ss=3D"copy-to-clipboard-button" type=3D"button" data-copy-state=3D"copy"><s=
pan>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div><p>If minikube fails to sta=
rt, see the <a href=3D"https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/drivers/">drivers =
page</a> for help setting up a compatible container or virtual-machine mana=
ger.</p>
<h2 class=3D"step"><span class=3D"fa-stack fa-1x"><i class=3D"fa fa-circle =
fa-stack-2x"></i><strong class=3D"fa-stack-1x text-primary">3</strong></spa=
n>Interact with your cluster</h2>
<p>If you already have kubectl installed (see <a href=3D"https://kubernetes=
.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl/">documentation</a>), you can now use =
it to access your shiny new cluster:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight"><div class=3D"code-toolbar"><pre tabindex=3D"0" st=
yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
-shell" data-lang=3D"shell">kubectl get po <span class=3D"token parameter v=
ariable">-A</span>
</code></pre><div class=3D"toolbar"><div class=3D"toolbar-item"><button cla=
ss=3D"copy-to-clipboard-button" type=3D"button" data-copy-state=3D"copy"><s=
pan>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div><p>Alternatively, minikube =
can download the appropriate version of kubectl and you should be able to u=
se it like this:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight"><div class=3D"code-toolbar"><pre tabindex=3D"0" st=
yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
-shell" data-lang=3D"shell">minikube kubectl -- get po <span class=3D"token=
 parameter variable">-A</span>
</code></pre><div class=3D"toolbar"><div class=3D"toolbar-item"><button cla=
ss=3D"copy-to-clipboard-button" type=3D"button" data-copy-state=3D"copy"><s=
pan>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div><p>You can also make your l=
ife easier by adding the following to your shell config: (for more details =
see: <a href=3D"https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/handbook/kubectl/">kubect=
l</a>)</p>
<div class=3D"highlight"><div class=3D"code-toolbar"><pre tabindex=3D"0" st=
yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
-shell" data-lang=3D"shell"><span class=3D"token builtin class-name">alias<=
/span> <span class=3D"token assign-left variable">kubectl</span><span class=
=3D"token operator">=3D</span><span class=3D"token string">"minikube kubect=
l --"</span>
</code></pre><div class=3D"toolbar"><div class=3D"toolbar-item"><button cla=
ss=3D"copy-to-clipboard-button" type=3D"button" data-copy-state=3D"copy"><s=
pan>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div><p>Initially, some services=
 such as the storage-provisioner, may not yet be in a Running state. This i=
s a normal condition during cluster bring-up, and will resolve itself momen=
tarily. For additional insight into your cluster state, minikube bundles th=
e Kubernetes Dashboard, allowing you to get easily acclimated to your new e=
nvironment:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight"><div class=3D"code-toolbar"><pre tabindex=3D"0" st=
yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
-shell" data-lang=3D"shell">minikube dashboard
</code></pre><div class=3D"toolbar"><div class=3D"toolbar-item"><button cla=
ss=3D"copy-to-clipboard-button" type=3D"button" data-copy-state=3D"copy"><s=
pan>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div><h2 class=3D"step"><span cl=
ass=3D"fa-stack fa-1x"><i class=3D"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i><strong cl=
ass=3D"fa-stack-1x text-primary">4</strong></span>Deploy applications</h2>
<div class=3D"code-tabs">
    <ul class=3D"nav nav-tabs"><li class=3D"nav-tab active"><a href=3D"http=
s://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/start/?arch=3D%2Flinux%2Fx86-64%2Fstable%2Fbi=
nary+download#Service" class=3D"nav-tab">Service</a></li><li class=3D"nav-t=
ab"><a href=3D"https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/start/?arch=3D%2Flinux%2Fx=
86-64%2Fstable%2Fbinary+download#LoadBalancer" class=3D"nav-tab">LoadBalanc=
er</a></li><li class=3D"nav-tab"><a href=3D"https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/do=
cs/start/?arch=3D%2Flinux%2Fx86-64%2Fstable%2Fbinary+download#Ingress" clas=
s=3D"nav-tab">Ingress</a></li></ul>
    <div class=3D"tab-content">
<div class=3D"tab-pane active" title=3D"Service">
    <p>Create a sample deployment and expose it on port 8080:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight"><div class=3D"code-toolbar"><pre tabindex=3D"0" st=
yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
-shell" data-lang=3D"shell">kubectl create deployment hello-minikube <span =
class=3D"token parameter variable">--image</span><span class=3D"token opera=
tor">=3D</span>kicbase/echo-server:1.0
kubectl expose deployment hello-minikube <span class=3D"token parameter var=
iable">--type</span><span class=3D"token operator">=3D</span>NodePort <span=
 class=3D"token parameter variable">--port</span><span class=3D"token opera=
tor">=3D</span><span class=3D"token number">8080</span>
</code></pre><div class=3D"toolbar"><div class=3D"toolbar-item"><button cla=
ss=3D"copy-to-clipboard-button" type=3D"button" data-copy-state=3D"copy"><s=
pan>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div><p>It may take a moment, bu=
t your deployment will soon show up when you run:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight"><div class=3D"code-toolbar"><pre tabindex=3D"0" st=
yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
-shell" data-lang=3D"shell">kubectl get services hello-minikube
</code></pre><div class=3D"toolbar"><div class=3D"toolbar-item"><button cla=
ss=3D"copy-to-clipboard-button" type=3D"button" data-copy-state=3D"copy"><s=
pan>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div><p>The easiest way to acces=
s this service is to let minikube launch a web browser for you:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight"><div class=3D"code-toolbar"><pre tabindex=3D"0" st=
yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
-shell" data-lang=3D"shell">minikube <span class=3D"token function">service=
</span> hello-minikube
</code></pre><div class=3D"toolbar"><div class=3D"toolbar-item"><button cla=
ss=3D"copy-to-clipboard-button" type=3D"button" data-copy-state=3D"copy"><s=
pan>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div><p>Alternatively, use kubec=
tl to forward the port:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight"><div class=3D"code-toolbar"><pre tabindex=3D"0" st=
yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
-shell" data-lang=3D"shell">kubectl port-forward service/hello-minikube <sp=
an class=3D"token number">7080</span>:8080
</code></pre><div class=3D"toolbar"><div class=3D"toolbar-item"><button cla=
ss=3D"copy-to-clipboard-button" type=3D"button" data-copy-state=3D"copy"><s=
pan>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div><p>Tada! Your application i=
s now available at <a href=3D"http://localhost:7080/">http://localhost:7080=
/</a>.</p>
<p>You should be able to see the request metadata in the application output=
. Try changing the path of the request and observe the changes. Similarly, =
you can do a POST request and observe the body show up in the output.</p>
</div>
<div class=3D"tab-pane" title=3D"LoadBalancer">
    <p>To access a LoadBalancer deployment, use the =E2=80=9Cminikube tunne=
l=E2=80=9D command. Here is an example deployment:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight"><div class=3D"code-toolbar"><pre tabindex=3D"0" st=
yle=3D"background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webk=
it-text-size-adjust:none;" class=3D"language-shell"><code class=3D"language=
